SEARCH

All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AbstractParser
Abstract Parser - Parses a text file and extracts data (sets of words, mappings etc.).
AbstractThreadedParser
Abstract Threaded Parser - Leverages virtual threads to parse a text file and extract data (sets of words, mappings etc.).
CommonWordsParser
Common Words Parser - Leverages virtual threads to efficiently extract a set of commonly used words from a file.
DictionaryParser
Dictionary Parser - Leverages virtual threads to efficiently create a mapping of words in a dictionary file to their definitions.
Filter
Filter - Intakes keySets from dictionary, filters sets by removing common words from words found in users file, then retains only the remaining words that are also found in the dictionary.
IndexEntry
IndexEntry - Contains details related to parsed words (dictionary definition and pages on which each word appeared).
Indexer
Indexer - Encapsulates index generating process, delegates responsibilities to relevant classes.
MapBuilder
Map Builder - Creates a mapping of filtered words to definitions and lists of pages.
Menu
Menu - Manages display of menus, handles user inputs for paths and extra options.
Outputter
Outputter - Methods for outputting complete indexes to file or console.
Parsator
Parsator - Acts as template or contract for inheriting subtypes.
Runner
Runner for Multithreaded Indexing API version 1.0.
UserInputParser
User Input Parser - Parses user-specified file, extracts a mapping of words found to pages they were found on.
